\begin{block}{Approximate Bayesian Computation (ABC)}
\begin{itemize}
    \item a random sample of parameters is drawn
    \item a data simulated from the sample parameter is compared to the actual data using summary statistics (mean proportion of sex and infected and variation in mean across time/space)
    \item if the difference is small enough, the parameter sample that generated the data is \emph{accepted}
    \item the process is repeated but parameters are sampled from deviates of the aceepted parameters and lower acceptance rate is used
\end{itemize}
\end{block}

