\begin{alertblock}{Discussion and further questions}
\begin{itemize}
    \item High asexual diversity \cite{dagan2013clonal} and different environment (e.g., seasonal flood \cite{ben2007temporal} and highly interconnected sites \cite{dagan2013clonal}) may not be appropriate for the Red Queen Hypothesis?
    \item Detecting a positive correlation is not easy; [CITE] used a simple model. What about [CITE]?
    \item expected relationship may be masked by different cycles but may be recovered with high spatial mixing
    \item try test for risk rather than looking at prevalence?
\end{itemize}
\end{alertblock}


